      "bullets": [
        "Acoustic injection attacks use ultrasound to exploit MEMS microphones, allowing remote command execution on voice-enabled PCs without physical access.",
        "Malware can repurpose audio output jacks and speakers into microphones, bypassing OS microphone permissions to record local ambient audio silently.",
        "Targeted acoustic frequencies can induce resonance in MEMS accelerometers or mechanical hard drives, leading to physical denial-of-service or data corruption."
      ]
