      "bullets": [
        "GitHub locks DevOps into proprietary features like Actions, Issues, and PRs, making migrations to GitLab or Forgejo incredibly complex.",
        "Centralizing Git hosting creates single points of failure, risking CI/CD pipelines and package registries during widespread GitHub platform outages.",
        "GitHub replaces native, distributed Git protocols with proprietary APIs and web UIs, hindering offline development and open-source interoperability."
      ]
